RPLOG

This command shows you your RP log. Your RP log
contains the last 5 RP things your character
has seen, including emotes, poses, says and so
on.

#0
TELLS

Usage: "tells"

This command shows you your tell buffer. Your tell
buffer contains the last 10 tells you've got, even
if you got them while you were link-dead or while
you were posting/mailing/writing anything.

A new, added feature, is that the tell is able
to be retrieved even if the person that sent it
has subsequently logged off the MUD!
#0
wolfsense
Usage: wolfsense <player|mob>

Wolfsense is a Wolfkin guild skill which allows you to seek out
either a player character or a mobile object. Wolfsense even
gives you a chance to find a player character even if they are
hiding his or her tracks, since wolfkin have an enhanced ability
to smell them out.
#0
wolfcall
Usage: wolfcall

Wolfcall is a Wolfkin guild skill which allows you to rally wolves
to your aid. The number of wolves that come to your aid is random but
based on the wolf mobile objects that are in the vicinity of your
character.
#0
GHELP
Usages: 

'ghelp <guild name/num>' : Shows all ghelp entries in one of your guilds.
'ghelp <guild name/num> <ghelp keyword>' : Shows a specific ghelp entry.
'ghelp <guild name/num> write <existing/new ghelp keyword>' : Write a
       new entry or update an existing one.
'ghelp <guild name/num> remove <existing ghelp keyword>' : Remove an entry.


Remember, after updating or creating a ghelp entry, use the &wsaveguild&n command
#0
