LWEAPON
Usage: lweapon <target>

This command retrieves the Action Description of the 
targets wielded weapons, and displays them to you.

The description can be made using the tool skill.
#0
lweapon
Usage: lweapon <target>

This command retrieves the Action Description of the 
targets wielded weapons, and displays them to you.

The description can be made using the tool skill.
#0
"WARD HUMAN"

&nUsage: weave 'ward human'
Duration: Instant
Basic mana cost: 500
Cost in trains: 6
Minimum levels: Air: 0  Earth: 0  Fire: 0  Spirit: 20  Water: 0
Effect:
This weave wards the rooms adjacent to yours, so that you will detect the
approach of any people nearby. If someone passes through the ward, you will get
the message "Something triggered your ward!" If the weave fails, you will not
get a message, nor will the mana cost be affected - it will look as if the weave
worked, only it didn't :)

#0
TRIP
&nTrip is an attack similar to bash or stun. The idea is to kick the legs
from under your opponent - causing them to fall on their butt. :)
The better your % in trip, the more chance of victory. However, there
are some animals that can't be tripped, and a failed trip lands -you-
on your backside instead.

As with almost any combat skill, after using trip, you cannot use it again
for a few rounds of combat.

&ySEE ALSO: KICK,RESCUE,BACKSTAB,DIRTKICK,BASH,STUN,DISARM&n

