SMACK
This social is used to smack someone upside the head, as a form of
punishment or to make them see sense. Try smacking yourself for a laugh. :)
#0
PARRY DUCK SHIELDBLOCK DODGE

These skills are all automatic defense skills that take effect when attacked.
Depending on your skill, there is a chance that a \c01[Hit]\c00 will become a
\c02[Miss]\c00. If you're lucky. :)


See also: JUMP
#0
PARRY DUCK SHIELDBLOCK DODGE

These skills are all automatic defense skills that take effect when attacked.
Depending on your skill, there is a chance that a \c01[Hit]\c00 will become a
\c02[Miss]\c00. If you're lucky. :)
#0
BREAKSHIELD

Breakshield is a command available to all channeler and wilder class players.
Simply type 'breakshield' while shielded and you'll smash through - that is,
if you're strong enough. :) There is also a 'breakshield' spell/skill
available for channelers and wilders. It performs no differently to the command
breakshield, and costs 8 trains, so don't get it :)
#0
IC
Any given character can either be IC or OOC at any given time. Type:
&rTOGGLE IC&n to switch to In Character mode. Now, you will be In Character
where you are on the MUD (you cannot claim to be Out of Character if someone
wishes to Roleplay with you in the room you are in). All your channeling is
considered to be IC - and if you overchannel, you burn out. Your taint, if
you are a male channeler, may increase with various results.

You can always switch to In Character mode simply by typing this command;
nothing can prevent you from Roleplaying whenever you feel like it.
&rTOGGLE IC&n again to switch to Out of Character mode. Now, you will be considered
to be Out of Character wherever you are. You may still burn out, and, of
course, channeling is still IC. On the other hand, you cannot see what
In Character people are saying or doing while in this mode.
#0
IC.
