#0
DISGUISE GUILDDISGUISE
These commands allow you to disguise yourself.

Usages:
* "disguise <name>" will disguise you into someone else, 
   allowing you to set a new description, title and so on.
* "guilddisguise <guild name/num> <rank num> <subrank>"
   will add your disguised identity into a guild.

Some comments:
1) You can't guilddisguise into more than 1 exclusive 
   guild.
2) You can see all guilds' ranks using the "ranks <guild>"
   command.
3) Your darkfriend indentity will "pass" through the
   guilddisguising.
4) To undesguise use "disguise off".
#0
! ^

Use ! to repeat the last command typed at the keyboard.

Use ^ to replace a string from the last command with a new string.  The
syntax is the same as in csh: "^old-string^replacement"

Examples:

  > tell rasmusse Hi there, how are you?
  No-one by that name here.

  > ^rasmusse^rasmussen
  You tell Rasmussen, 'Hi there, how are you?'

  > ^you^you doing^
  You tell Rasmussen, 'Hi there, how are you doing?'

See also: ALIAS
#0
ALLGUILDS

This command will show you the list of all the guilds
which exist in the game, sorted by guild types.
#0
CLUBS

This command will show you the list of all the clubs
which exist in the game.
#0
MYGUILDS

Use this command to see all your guild information.
It will display the guilds you are a part of, your
status in them (GL, member, seeker), your guild
channel status (on/off), your guild permissions,
your guild ranks and subranks and how much you
withdrew/deposited in the guild bank account.
#0
GADMININFO

This useful GL command will show you all the guild's
administrative information: Ranks, Gzones, Gequipment,
Gskills, Guild flags, and so on.
 
If you are a GL, you can use "gadmininfo <guild name/id>"
to see your guild's stats.
#0
GUILDSET

This command is the basic command used to administer the
guild system. Some sub commands can be used by GLs, and
some can be used exclusively by the Admins. This command
will allow us to define the guilds, administer them and
set them up properly, all online.

In general, the command takes tose parameters:
    guildset <guild number/name> <field> <value>

Field              Level         Value type     Description
=====              =====         ==========     ===========

gl_title           LVL_GRGOD,      MISC     For setting the GL title
guildie_titles     LVL_GRGOD,      MISC     For setting the guildies' title
gossip_name        LVL_GRGOD,      MISC     For setting the gossip name
guild_filename     LVL_GRGOD,      MISC     Filename of guild file
id                 LVL_GRGOD,      NUMBER   Guild's id number
name               LVL_GRGOD,      MISC     Guild's name
type               LVL_GRGOD,      NUMBER   Guild's type
f_exclusive        LVL_GRGOD,      BINARY   Exclusive flag
f_ic               LVL_GRGOD,      BINARY   IC flag
f_gltitle          LVL_GRGOD,      BINARY   Do the GLs have a title?
f_guildiestitle    LVL_GRGOD,      BINARY   Do the guildies have a title?
f_gossip           LVL_GRGOD,      BINARY   Does the guild have gossip?
f_nogchan          LVL_GRGOD,      BINARY   Does the guild have a gchan?
f_secretive        1,              BINARY   Is the guild secretive?
f_noglist          1,              BINARY   Could guildies use glist?
f_nogwho           1,              BINARY   Could guildies use who -g?
gold               LVL_GRGOD,      NUMBER   For setting the guild's gold
guildwalk          LVL_GRGOD,      NUMBER   For setting a guildwalk room   
gchan_name         1,              MISC     For setting the gchannel name
gchan_color        1,              MISC     For setting the gchannel color
gchan_type         1,              NUMBER   For setting the gchannle type
gequipadd          LVL_GRGOD,      NUMBER   For adding gequipment
gequipremove       LVL_GRGOD,      NUMBER   For removing gequipment
gskilladd          LVL_GRGOD,      MISC     For adding gskills
gskillremove       LVL_GRGOD,      MISC     For removing gskills
gzoneadd           LVL_GRGOD,      NUMBER   For adding gzones
gzoneremove        LVL_GRGOD,      NUMBER   For removing gzones
grankadd           1,              MISC     For adding ranks
grankremove ,      1,              NUMBER   For removing ranks
f_noguildwalk      LVL_GRGOD,      BINARY   Does the guild have guildwalk?
f_nobank           LVL_GRGOD,      BINARY   Does the guild have a bank account?
f_dark             LVL_GRGOD,      BINARY   Is this a dark guild?
f_disguise_stay    LVL_GRGOD,      BINARY   Guild sticks through disguise?
grankchange        1,              MISC     Changes a grank's name

Some special uses:

* guildset <guild name/id> gskilladd <maximum set> <skill name>
  for example: guildset Aiel gskilladd 80 kick

  guildset <guild name/id> gskillremove <skill name>
  for example: guildset Aiel gskillremove kick

* guildset <guild name/id> grankadd <rank number> <rank name>
  for example: guildset Aiel grankadd 5 Deran's Pet
  Notice that you can either add to the end of the rank list, or
  to its middle. Adding to its middle will "push" all already 
  set ranks "one place" forward. Use the "gadmininfo" command to
  see your guild's rank list.

  guildset <guild name/id> grankremove <rank number>
  Notice that if you remove a rank from the middle of the rank
  list, all other ranks will be "pushed" backward one place.

* guildset <guild name/id> grankchange <rank number> <new name>

#0
GUILDIESET
  
This command is mostly for the Guildleaders, so they can set
their guildies' guild stats and permissions.

The command's syntax is as follows:
  guildieset <guild number/name> <guildie name> <field> <value>

Field           Level      Value type  Description
=====           =====      ==========  ===========

gchan           1,           BINARY    Turn guild channel on/off
gl              LVL_GRGOD,   BINARY    Make a guildie into a GL
perm_guild      1,           BINARY    Give guildie perm to guild seekers
perm_withdraw   1,           BINARY    Perm to use gwithdraw
perm_gossip     1,           BINARY    Perm to write guild gossip
perm_sponsor    1,           BINARY    Perm to sponsor seekers
perm_authorize  1,           BINARY    Perm to authorize seekers
rank            1,           NUMBER    For setting ranks on guildies
perm_gskillset  1,           BINARY    Perm to use "gskillset"
authorized      1,           BINARY    For authorizing a seeker
subrank         1,           MISC      For setting subranks
status_warder   1,           BINARY    For old system support   

Some important things:

* Notice that if you give a guildie the permission to authorize
  seekers, he could also use guildieset to authorize seekers.   

* Notice that subranks are now set per person. To set a subrank
  use "guildieset <guild name/id> <guildie name> subrank <subrank>"
  For example: "guildieset Aiel Deran subrank Clown

* Use the rank number to set a rank. The rank list you can find 
  in gadmininfo. For example: "guildieset Aiel Dulban rank 4"

* Setting status_warder only applies for the Tower and the Rebels.
