#0
GUILD-SYSTEM
 
Our new guild system is quite extensive, and it has
many features. Those features allow better running
of the guilds, an overall flexibility and many        
tools to enhance the guild experience and RP.

First thing you should do is type "allguilds" to
see our guild list. You can then check the info on
each guild by typing "guildinfo <guild name/num>"
(like "guildinfo Aiel"). You can start seeking a
guild by typing "seekguild <guild name/num>", but
remember, you can only seek and be a part of 1
exclusive guild. This means you can join multiple
guilds, as long as only one of them is exclusive 
and your background "supports" it. In "guildinfo"
you'll also find other important information, like
who are the Guildleaders of a guild, a full
description of the guild, and the requirements
needed to be a part of the guild.
There are also "clubs" in the game to be used
for various functions not connected to your char's
IC life. Type "clubs" to see a list of them.
 
Once in a guild, you could use a lot of guild
feautures:                                  

* Guild channel: The guild channel name can be
found in "guildinfo", and you can use it like any
other channel (For example: "tt Hello guys."). You
can toggle it on/off using "toggle <channel name>"
and you can toggle the channel tag by using
"toggle tag-<channel name>" (For example:
"toggle tag-tt"). Channel tags are useful when
you have more than one guild channel on.
Notice that the gdt command still works.
It will "point" to your guild's channel if you're 
a GL, to your exclusive guild if you're not a GL 
and are a part of an exclusive guild, and to a
random guild you are a part of otherwise.

* Guild gossip: Most guilds have a guild gossip,
and you can find its name in "guildinfo". Type
the guild gossip name and read the latest plots
and gossip in the guild.

* Guild help: Use the "ghelp" command to see a    
list of all the guild help entries and read them.
"ghelp <guild name/id>" will show you a list of
all the ghelp entries in one of your guilds (For
example: "ghelp Aiel"), and "ghelp <guild> <entry>"
is used to read a specific entry (For example:
"ghelp Aiel Guild-Policy"). Check out the guild
help entries for guild policies and various info
important for the guildies to know.

* Guild recall: Use "recall <guild name/num>" to
recall to the guild's main room.

* Guild bank accounts: Using the gdeposit and 
gwithdraw commands.

These are only minor examples. Check out the 
help entries below for more information on all
the cool features :)

Help entry         Description of the command
==========         ==========================
help allguilds     Lists all guilds in Fang.
help myguilds      Full info on your guilds.
help clubs         Lists all clubs.
help guildinfo     Info on a specific guild.
help seekguild     For seeking a guild.
help seeking       List of seekers in a guild.
help sponsor       For sponsoring seekers.
help glist         Lists all guildies in a guild.
help gdeposit      Deposit money in guild bank.
help gwithdraw     Withdraw money from guild.
help gskillset     For setting gskills.
help guild         For guilding chars.
help deguild       For deguilding chars.
help gadmininfo    For getting guild admin info.
help guildieinfo   For getting guildie info.
help guildset      For setting guild specs.
help guildieset    For setting guildie specs.
help gdesc         For setting guild desc.
help greq          For setting guild require'.
help saveguild     For saving guild info.
help gload         For loading guild equip.
