#0
ADT AMT BDT CLUBTALK CTELL DT GDT MDT TT WT
All these commands have to do with "channels", groups of people communicating.

ADT is for people within a certain Ajah
BDT, MDT and AMT are for people who are connected by a Bond, i.e., a Sedai and her Warders.
DT is for people within the Darkfriend guild.
GDT is for people within a guild.
OT is for Ogiers.
TT is for people guilded within a Tower guild, that is, Warders and Sedai.
WT is for Wolfkin.
CTELL is for people within a certain Aiel clan.
CLUBTALK is for people within a club made with the old club system.

If you are within the right groups you can use the these commands for communication.
If nothing else is stated, these channels are considered to be IC.
Due to the new &Cguild-system&n, the command for a guild channel can vary markedly.
Some of these channels can be switched on or off with the TOGGLE command.

See also: TOGGLE, GUILD-SYSTEM
