Usage: cart <room name>. 

A generic version of the taxi system. If you have 1500 gold, are in an 
OUTSIDE room (i.e, not indoors), know the name of the room you wish 
to travel to, and there's a path between these rooms (No closed doors, 
etc..) you can use this command for an easy travel there. 

See also: SPEEDWALK
#0
CEMOTE

Usage: cemote <same sex>|<opposite sex>|<nonchans>

This is a special variant of emote that only channelers can use.
It's intended use is to emote channeling, hence the name.
Since people see things differently depending on their gender and
ability to channel, the emote has to be split three ways:
* One for channelers of the same sex
* One for channelers of the opposite sex
* One for people who cannot channel.
The separator between those three parts is a tilde (|).

The first part is what channelers of the same sex see when the actor is
cemoting. That works just like an ordinary emote, with name first.
The two others however, are echoed "as is" without any name, since 
people who can't see the flows can't know who's responsible for what
happens due to them...Let's take an example:

cemote smiles as he sets Reorx beard on fire with Fire and Spirit|Your
skin itches as Reorx beard suddenly catches fire! Foul play!|All of a
sudden, Reorx beard self ignites!

Channelers of the same sex then see:
\c02Fredrik smiles as he sets Reorx beard on fire with Fire and Spirit\c00
and channelers of the opposite sex see:
\c02Your skin itches as Reorx beard suddenly catches fire!Foul play!\c00
and all the rest see:
\c02All of a sudden, Reorx beard self ignites!\c00

Play with it to see what you can use it for, it's not that apparent at
first glance.

See also: EMOTE POSE PEMOTE LASTEMOTE
#0
CHAR CONS DEXT HITP INTE MANA MOVE STRE WISD

These commands are all used at the trainer when you want to increase your stats.
They are all the first four letters of a stat.
By typing this, you either increase Charisma, Constitution, Dexterity, Intelligence,
Strength or Wisdom by one point or Mana, Move or Hitpoints by ten points.
The cost to raise Mana, Move or Hitpoints is one train per ten points.
The cost to raise the others vary, depending on how high stat you got:
 1-18 - 1 train
19-25 - 2 trains
26-30 - 3 trains
Raising to higher than 30 is not possible.
