#0
DICE

This is a fairly complex command that is used for selecting person to play with, set
the amount to be diced about, and finally to roll the dice.
The way it is performed is the following:

Dice <playername>

This selects the player you want to play with. The person has to be in the room.
If someone wants to dice with you and has typed this, you respond by typing

Dice <asking player's name>

Then you have confirmed that you two want to play dice.
After that, you have to set an amount to play about. This is done with the 
following command:

Dice <amount>

This makes one player set the amount he wants to play dice about. If you
accept his bet, you type the same. Otherwise, just walk away. *grin*
Then you play, by just typing

Dice

This rolls the dice and shows the results. The loser then automatically
loses the amount agreed upon, and the money is transferred to the winner.
After this, you can either decide to play again, by typing

Dice <amount>

which repeats the betting and dicing procedure, or by typing

Dice off

The last command stops the playing.
#0
DIRTKICK "DIRT KICK"

Dirt kick is an attempt to kick dirt in your opponents eye, in order
to render him/her/it blind. A succesfull attempt will blind your opponent, 
making him easier to hit, and give him a harder time to hit you. 

Examples: 

  > dirt Otto

Note, that after a dirtkick attempt, you will be unable to use this 
command for 2-5 rounds of violence, depending on how well you've
succeeded, or failed for that matter. 

See also: BACKSTAB,BASH,KICK,TRIP,
PUNCH,RESCUE,STUN,DISARM,WASH
#0
DISARM
DISARM

Disarm will allow you to attempt to disarm your opponent, thus forcing
him/her/it to fight without weapon. If your opponent is wielding two
weapons, both of 'em will be removed.

Examples:
  
  > disarm Perry

Note, that as well for all the other fighting-skills, you will not be 
able to use this skills for a couple of rounds, after an attempt. 

See also: BACKSTAB,BASH,DIRTKICK,KICK,RESCUE,PUNCH,STUN 
#0
