#0
INSTRUCT
Usage: Instruct <player> <skillname>

This command makes you teach a pupil a skill that you know.

For it to work, the following preconds must be met: \c04
- Both players must be in the same room for ten ticks in a row.
- You must have at least 80% in the skill you want to teach.
- The pupil mustn't have the skill
- The pupil must have sufficient amount of trains, since the cost for
  the pupil is the same as if he would have bought it at the trainer.
  (the cost depends on the skill and your class)
- If it's a spell, pupil must have the required flowstrengths.
\c00
After you have successfully trained someone, you have to wait ten
more minutes.
