#0
MAINTAIN

When maintaining a weave, each tick, the MUD will go through all the weaves
and when encountering one of yours, an ammount of mana will be deducted for 
the maintaining. In exchange, the duration of the weave will not lessen that
tick. 

The ammount of mana deducted each tick will be displayed to you, but can be 
calculated like this. (base-mana+mana_add)/duration.

If you go to sleep, quit the game, release the One/True power or if you
get killed ALL your maintained weaves will unravel. 

A tied weave will have a set duration. No additional mana will be deducted, 
but once the duration is ended, the weave will unravel. 

Tie is a command that'll allow you to tie off a maintained weave. 
Unknot will untie a tied weave, and you'll start to maintain it instead.
Unravel will 'destroy' a weave, whether it's tied or maintained. (Maintained 
weaves will be harder to unravel though.) If you try to unravel a weave that
you yourself has woven, you will automagically succeed. 

Syntax:
  tie 'armor' kilmor 
     Will tie the armor weave you've woven earlier on Kilmor
  unknot 'infravision'
     Will unknot the weave infravision, and since no target is given, it'll 
     unknot the infravision you've (hopefully) woven on yourself.
  unravel 'dome of air' 
     You will make an attempt to unravel the weave 'dome of air' that someone
     has wovem in the room you're in. If you're the weaver, it'll unravel 
     automagically.
#0
CHECK MAIL RECEIVE

Usage: check
       mail <recipient1> <recipient2> <recipient3> <recipient4> <recipient5>
       receive
       

The commands used by the Caemlyn Mail System (CMS) are MAIL, CHECK, and
RECEIVE.  CHECK and RECEIVE can be used at any location in the world, 
only MAIL must be used in an Official MMS Post Office. 
You can send mail to up to 5 people at one time.

Examples:

  To check and see if you have any mail waiting:
  > check

  To write mail to Niandra:
  > mail Niandra

  To ask the Postmaster to give you your mail, if you have any waiting:
  > receive

Stamps cost 1 coin. You must buy 1 stamp for each recipient.
