#0
PEMOTE

Usage pemote <target> <string for target>|<string for rest of room>

This command will do a 'targetted' emote. A certain string will
be emoted to the target character, the other (optional) string
will be emoted to the resto f the characters in room.

Example:

> pemote Otto thinks you're an utter bastard.|thinks Otto is an utter bastard. 

Will display to you as:
You: Benke thinks you're an utter bastard.

Will display to Otto:
Benke thinks you're an utter bastard.

And lastly, the rest of the room will see:
Benke thinks Otto is an utter bastard.

The last string is optional, so you might send an emote to the 
target alone. 

See also: EMOTE, CEMOTE, POSE, LASTEMOTE
#0
POSE

Usage: pose <pose string>

This command is quite similar to the Gleeman SFX.

However, unlike emote, your name doesn't have to be in the string. 
in the string. 

Example:

> pose Leaping to his feet, Benke draws his sword quicker than the eye can see. 

The room will see the following:

Leaping to his feet, Benke draws his sword quicker than the eye can see. (Benke)

See also: CEMOTE, EMOTE, PEMOTE, LASTEMOTE
#0
POUR

Usage: pour <from container> <to container>
       pour <from container> out

If you want to pour some liquid from one container to another.  Pouring
