#0
POWERTRAP

Usage: powertrap 'aggrospellname' <condition>

This skill command is used to lay traps for other people with the help of
the One Power. It basically lays a dormant spell waiting for a condition to
trigger on.

You can only have one powertrap per room, and only aggressive spells are
viable for powertraps.

The available triggers are:
\c01human\c00 - makes the spell trigger whenever a human enters the room
\c01channeler\c00 - makes a spell trigger whenever a channeler enters the room
\c01shadowspawn\c00 - makes a spell trigger whenever a shadowspawn enters the room
\c01xxx\c00 - any positive number, indicating a delay of xxx ticks before it goes off

You can not combine triggers, nor can you add mana to powertrapped spells, nor do
powertraps survive game reboots.

The mana cost for a failed attempt to set a powertrap is \c02200\c00 mana, for
a successful one, the spells basic mana cost.
#0
PRACTICE 

Usage: practice [skill or weave name]

Practice is the way you improve your weaves and skills.  You can only do
so at certain locations, where a Trainer is located.   Type
"practice <skill>" to improve your abilitie. You can only practice a skill
up to 70%, after that you can only get better by using the skill. 

If you type practice anywhere other than in the rpesence of a trainer you will
get a list of all of the weaves and skills you know and your level of
proficiency at each.
#0
PRAY NOPRAY

Usage: pray
       nopray

Pray is a newbie command to send a message to every online immortal that you need
help in the room you are standing in. It is advised that if you type pray, do
not move, so someone can come to the room you are in, or send you a tell. If no one
replies to your pray, try asking for help on the Question channel or in a tell to a
Newbie Helper. As this is considered a newbie command, you can only use it up to
level 20.

Nopray is an immortal command to turn off a player's ability to pray before the
player reaches level 20. This ought only to be set if the player is spamming by
typing pray over and over again in succession.

See Also: QUESTION
#0
PULL DONTPULL

Syntax: pull (wagonname)
        dontpull
        
By typing the first, you begin dragging a wagon after you (if you have one in the
room, that is), and by typing the second, you stop dragging the wagon.
#0
PUNCH

Gives your opponent a powerful punch. The damage of the punch will increase 
with increasing levels. After a punch attempt you will be unable to punch again
for a few rounds of violence, just like with BASH and KICK etc..

Examples:

 > punch Kentklas

See also: BACKSTAB,BASH,DIRTKICK,DISARM,KICK,PUNCH,RESCUE,STUN
