#0
QUIT

When you get tired of playing, you can leave the game by typing 'quit'.
#0
READ

Usage: read <object>
       read <board message number>
       read <name of mail sender>

Command used for reading posts, mails and notes.

Examples:
           "read note"
           "read mail"
           "read 2.mail"
           "read 25"  (for reading post number 25)
           "read deran"  (for reading your mail from deran)

See also: BOARDS, WRITE, REMOVE
#0
RECALL

Usage: recall [guild <name/id>]

This command, by itself, recalls to the recall room. You must be OOC, but
there is no other restriction or penalty.

When used as a guild recall, it will take you to the recall room of the
guild you chose. Again, you must be OOC, but as a side-effect, your
current moves will be lowered - the amount depends on both your current
and maximum moves. If you have a large number of moves, it will take
300. The lower your moves, the less it will take, but you can always
recall guild, even if you have 0 moves.
#0
RELEASE

Syntax: release

This is the command to use when you want to let go of the One Power and
not use any more weaves for the moment. It is a wise thing to do 
immediately, because holding on to the One Power costs mana each tick...

See also: GRASP WEAVE
#0
