       remove all
       remove all.<keyword>
&n       remove <number of message on a board>

This is used to remove an item you have on you, or a post you have made.

Examples:

  > remove boots
  > remove sword
  > remove all
  > remove all.bronze

See also: GRAB, HOLD, WEAR, WIELD, READ, WRITE
#0
REPAIR

Usage: repair <item>


This skill command attempts to repair an item you have in your inventory.
A failed repair attempt will cost you the items value divided by 20,
a successful attempt 1/10.

You can also use this command at the \c02repair shop\c00, n, e of Oval, even
though you don't have the skill, but it will cost more then; 1/5 the
items value.
#0
REPLY

Usage: reply <message>

This command will send a reply to the last person to send you a message
using TELL.  It works just as if you had typed 'tell <player> <message>'
but makes it a bit easier.  It can also be very useful in case someone
invisible sends you a message.

Example:

Ras tells you, 'Hi!'
> reply hey
You tell Ras, 'hey'
>
Someone tells you, 'I am your secret admirer.'
> reply Who are you?
You tell someone, 'Who are you?'

See also: TELL, TOGGLE
#0
REPORT

Usage: report

This command sends a report of your current health to the other people in
your group.
#0
OREPORT

Usage: oreport

This command sends a report of your current health to everyone else in
the room.
#0
RESCUE

Usage: rescue <victim>

This command is useful if you want to try and make an attacker hit you
instead of your poor friend who is being pummeled.  You can only 'turn'
one monster for each rescue attempt.  This is very useful when playing
in groups, of course.

Example:

  > rescue Yankee
#0
SAVE

Usage: save

Save your persona.  This includes experience points, strength, gold, etc.
Your equipment is also saved in the (unlikely?) event of a crash.  The
game periodically auto-saves you and your equipment, so it is not necessary
to have your client auto-save you as well.

You CANNOT load a saved version if you die -- your persona still exists,
but you will lose experience, and all your objects stay in the game, with
your corpse.
#0
SAY OSAY TELL ASK WHISPER SHOUT '

Usage: osay | shout <string>
       tell | whisper | ask <player> <string>

If you consider communicating with other beings, you might be understood
better if you start your sentences with either osay, tell, whisper or shout.

If you frequent MUDs, you are probably used to using 'say' to talk.
Here at Dragon's Fang, however, the standard way to talk is with
'Osay' (&WO&nut of character &Wsay&n). Say is reserved for roleplay.

Examples:

&n  > osay Hey, does anyone know how to get to Emond's Field?
  > tell catje hi, how are you?

You can use , as shorthand for Osay, or ' for say.

&n  > , hello there

Shout broadcasts your message to everyone in your geographic zone.

See also: AUCTION, GOSSIP, GSAY, QSAY, REPLY, TOGGLE, ROLEPLAY

