#0
SLEEP

SLEEP is both a command and the name of a weave.

The SLEEP command puts you to sleep, allowing you to regain your health more
quickly.  You will be largely unaware of your surroundings while asleep.
You can awaken yourself with the WAKE command. The SLEEP command can also be
used with furniture , as in "sleep bed" (a more general description of the
command might be "sleep <furniture object>").

The SLEEP weave forces the victim into a magical sleep such that they cannot
be awakened until the weave wears off.

Usage       : weave 'sleep' <victim>
Accumulative: Yes (Duration)
Duration    : 4 hours + level/4
Level       : Mage level 8.

If failing saving throw versus weave, the person will fall asleep.
A person who is affected by sleep can only be awakened if attacked.

See also: WAKE LONGSLEEP
#0
SNEAK
Usage: sneak

Used for sneaking (moving in and out of rooms without anyone taking notice).
If the command succeeds, an (s) will appear in front of your prompt, and you
will receive the message 'Ok, you begin sneaking.' To stop sneaking, simply
type 'sneak' again.

See also: HIDE
#0
SPEEDWALK

Usage: speedwalk <room name>

This command allows you to speedwalk between room A(your current room)
and room B(room name), if and only if, you 'know' these two locations 
well, and granted that there's a path between the two rooms without 
any closed doors on the way. 

To 'learn' a room well enough to speedwalk from/too it, you must spend 
approximately 5 RL minutes in the room. A message'll tell you when you
have 'learned' it. 

See also: CART
#0
SPELLS

Usage: spells

NOTE: In the Wheel of Time terminology, what is usually refered to as a 
"spell" is called a \c01weave\c00 on Dragon's Fang.
This command can only be used by people who can channel.
When typed, you will see a list of all the spells that exist in the mud, and
what demands in the five Flows they've got to be able to gain them.

See also: GAIN, FLOW
#0
SPLIT

Usage: split <amount to split>

Split is used to split money among people in your group who are in the same
room as you.  If you are in a group with 4 other people, all of whom are in
the same room with you, and you type SPLIT 100, you will give each of the
other 4 group members 20 coins each.  (100 coins is split 5 ways; you keep
your share and give everyone else their share).

See also: FOLLOW, GROUP
#0
STEAL

Usage: steal <item> <victim>

Use steal to steal gold or items from people.  The chance of not getting
caught depends on how well you have practiced steal, and if the person
is asleep.

Examples:

  > steal gold drunk
  > steal sword mercenary
    (If it's wielded, only possible if he is sleeping)

See also: FLAGS
#0
STUN

Will give a stunning blow to your opponent, thus making him easier to hit, 
inflicting more damage to him, and, of course, rendering him unable to defend
himself. :)

If successful, your opponent will be stunned for 2-3 rounds of violence, and
of course, after a stun attempt, you will not be able to use stun again for a
few rounds. 

Exampels:

 > stun Demandred

See also: BACKSTAB,BASH,DIRTKICK,DISARM,KICK,PUNCH,RESCUE
