you can go.
With argument, you will be taken to that place for a cost of 200 coins.
#0
TEACH

Usage: teach <player> air/earth/fire/water/spirit

This skill enables you to teach members of your guild what you have
learned in the five weaves so far, sharing some insights and making
your student more adept and skilled.
What it does, in game terms, is give the student (only one at a time,
only those in the same guild) an increase in the flow you teach. 
After you've taught, you have to wait a while until you can teach again,
and a student can only be taught 15 times.
#0
TIE

If you have already woven a weave, and are maintaining it, you might 
wish to tie it of, in order to save mana. This is what tie allows you
to do. 
Remeber though, you can ONLY Tie weaves you yourself has woven.

Syntax: 
        tie 'weave' <target|room>

If no target is given, Tie will assume you wish to tie the particular
weave on yourself.

Examples:
       tie 'armor'
    Will try to locate, and tie an armor-weave on you.  

       tie `shield' lanfear
    Will try to locate a shield=weave on lanfear, that you are maintaining, 
    and if found, tie it off. 

       tie 'Dome of Air' room
    Will try to locate a Dome of Air in the room you're in and tie it off.
#0
TIEWEAVE

Tieweave works almost exactly like weave, with one main difference. Weave
will maintain weaves, thus costing you mana each tick for all the weaves
you're maintaining, while tieweave will tie your weave off, thus giving your 
weave a limited existance. Weaving none-tiable weaves with tieweave works very
well, i.e. they're more or less transparent. 

Syntax: 
        tieweave `weave` <target> <mana_add>

Examples:
        tieweave 'armor'
        tieweave 'shield' Mazrim

See also: WEAVE, MAINTAIN, TIE, UNKNOT, UNRAVEL
#0
TIME

Usage: time

Gives you the current game time.  Your initial reaction to the output of
this command may be one of surprise, but you'll get used to it.  You'll
have to, at any rate, since certain things in the game depend on this
particular notion of time; the opening hours of the shops, for example.
#0
TINFO

Usage: tinfo <object>

Will display info about a Ter'angreal (given that object indeed is a 
Ter'angreal), such as which weave will be woven, at what lvl, mana add, 
if the weave is aggressive or not, and what argument \c01USE\c00 expects
when using the Ter'angreal. 

Note: There's a 3% chance of burning out if failing!

See also: USE TTEST
#0
TITLE

Usage: title <new title>

Sets the title people see on the WHO list and when you're in the room with
them.  You can't use parentheses (the "(" and ")" characters) because those
are reserved for flags.

See also: FLAGS, WHO
#0
TOGGLE

Usage: toggle
       toggle <toggle>
       toggle afk|afw <optional message>

TOGGLE shows you the current values of various toggles available on the MUD.
Most of these toggles remain the same until you change them; i.e. they are
saved when you quit. The exception to this is AFK and AFW messages.

TOGGLE followed by a toggle name will toggle that toggle.

Afk and afw may have an optional message that will be sent to people trying 
to TELL you. If not set, the standard messages will be shown.

Example:
  > toggle afk I'm not here at the moment, try again later.
Okey-Dokey, you're now AFK.

  > toggle afk
You're no longer AFK. Enjoy!

Some items shown in the toggle display cannot be changed with the toggle command.
These are: 
  Hit/Move/Mana Display: set with the DISPLAY command
  Wimp level: set with the WIMPY command
  Color level: set with the COLOR command

Valid toggles are:
  Afk: Away from keyboard. Usage above.
  Afw: Away from window. Usage above.
  Auction: Show messages on the AUCTION channel.
  Autoassist: Automatically assist members of your group when they are attacked.
  Autoexit: Will show available exits when you look at a room. Note: closed doors
    are not shown.
  Autogold: Automatically take all the gold from the mob when you kill it.
  Autojunk: Automatically junk the corpse of a mob when you kill it.
  Autoloot: Automatically take all objects from a mob when you kill it.
  Autosplit: When Autogold is set, automatically split the gold with everyone in
    your group.
  Brief: Don't show room descriptions when you enter a room. Only use if you are
    familiar with the area. The LOOK command will always show room descriptions.
  Clubtalk: Display messages from your fellow club members on the CLUBTALK channel.
  Compact: Don't send an extra newline after each command. Useful if you have a
    small display.
  Death: Display death screams in your area.
  Dt: Display messages from your fellow darkfriends on the DT channel.
  Gdt: Show messages from your fellow guild members on the GDT channel.
  Hunger: Display hunger and thirst messages.
  Ic: In character.
  Lookahead: scan forward 2 rooms when moving.
  Nospam: Don't show fight messages.
  Notell: Prevent other players from being able to TELL you. When set (notell) will
    appear in your WHO listing.
  Obscene: Display messages on the OBSCENE channel.
  Ooc: Show messages on the OOC channel.
  Ot: Display messages from your Ogier brethren over the OT channel.
  Poseid: Display POSE identification.
  Pwimpy: Use a percentage for WIMPY, instead of number of hitpoints.
  Quest: Become part of the currently running quest. When set (quest) will appear in
    your WHO listing, and you'll be able to use QSAY to talk to other questors.
  Question: Show messages on the QUESTION channel.
  Repeat: Show your own communication back to you when you use commands such as TELL,
    SHOUT, OOC, etc.
  Shout: Show messages on the SHOUT channel, if off (deaf) will appear next to your
    WHO entry.
  Sliceweave: Attempt to slice weaves directed at you. Success depends mostly on
    your strength in FIRE and SPIRIT, compared to the weaver. Beware: you will pay
    half the MANA cost of the weave on each attempt. If you don't have enough MANA,
    the weave will automatically bypass this defense.
  Song: Display messages on the SING channel.
  Tt: Show messages from your fellow Tower members (ie. Sedai and Warders) on the
    TT channel.
  Wt: Show messages from fellow Wolfkin on the WT channel.

See also: AUCTION, CLUBTALK, DISPLAY, DT, GDT, FIRE, LOOK, MANA, OBSCENE, OT, POSE,
  QSAY, QUESTION, SCAN, SHOUT, SING, SPIRIT, TELL, TT, WHO, WIMPY, WT
