#0
UNKNOT

Sometimes you have tied of a weave, or pehaps used tieweave, and wish to 
resume maintaining a weave. This is what UNKNOT is for. Remeber, as with
Tie, you might only Unknot weaves you yourself has woven. Also, as with
Tie, if no argument is given, Unknot will autotarget you. 

Syntax: 
     unknot `weave` <target|room>

Examples:
     unknot 'armor'
 Will unknot the first found armor-weave on you, that you yourself has 
 woven.

     unknot 'shield' Kilmor
  Will unknot the first shield-weave you've woven on Rauuh, and set you to
  maintain it. 

     unknot 'Dome of Fire' room
  Will unknot the Dome of Fire (if any) weave in your present location and
  set you to maintain it instead.

See also: UNRAVEL UNKNOT WEAVE TIEWEAVE TIE 
#0
UNRAVEL

Unravel will try to 'destroy' a weave woven on a char (including yourself).
If you are the weaver, you will automagicall succeed to Unravel the weave, 
and at no mana-cost at all. If another player has woven the weave you want
to unravel, the difficulty will be different depending on if the weave is 
maintained, the mana_add the weaver has put into the weave, the Power the
weave is woven with (I.e harder to unravel a weave woven with Saidin, if
you yourself is wielding Saidar).

Although, unravel as tied off weave, woven with the same power as you
yourself wield, you will always have a chance between 10-100% of success. 
And your mana will never go below 50).

If the weave is maintained, it will cost double amount of mana, and reduce
the chans of succes with half, to unravel. 

If the weave is woven with the 'wrong' Power, it will once again reduce the 
chans of success with 50%. 

So, trying to unravel a maintained weave, woven with the 'wrong' Power
will cost yuo double as much mana as a tied of weave, and your chans
of success will be between 2-25%.

If target is omitted, unravel will autotarget on you. 

Syntax:
   unravel 'weave' <target|room>

Examples:
   unravel 'wrap' 
 Will try to unravel the first wrap-weave found on yourself.

   unravel 'shield' Mazrim
 Will try to unravel the first shield-weave found on Mazrim

   unravel 'Dome of Air' room
 Will try to unravel the dome of air-weave in your present location.
 
#0
UPTIME

Usage: uptime

This command simple tells you how long the mud has been running since the 
last reboot/crash.
#0
USE

Usage: use <argument(s)>

Using a Ter'angreal is done in two steps:

1) make sure you're holding the Ter'angreal. 
2) use the USE command together with arguments the Ter'angreal requires. 

For instance, a Ter'angreal containing a Travel weave, will need a
roomname as argument, either the new or the old syntax:

  (old)use Caemlyn 
  (new)use 'Caemlyn Pigeon Courier'

A Ter'angreal weaving offensive weaves, or weaves like heal, shield will
require a character name as argument. If the weave can be applied to yourself, 
no argument will be nescessary. 

See also: TER'ANGREAL TINFO TTEST
#0
