#0
WEAVE CAST

Usage: weave 'weave name' 
       weave 'weave name' <mana add>
       weave 'weave name' <target>
       weave 'weave name' <target> <mana add>
       
This is the command to use spells, or "weaves" as they are called in
Dragons Fang Mud. In order to be able to use the weaves, you must have
learned Grasp, Release and the particular weave you want to use.
Once that is done, you type one of the above mentioned syntaxes,
depending on whether the weave needs a target mentioned or not. The 
<mana add> is how much (if any) -extra- mana you want to spend on the
weave to increase its performance. Exactly what that increase is for
the particular weave is described individually for each weave.
Remember, though, that the total mana used in a weave always is the 
"Basic Mana cost" mentioned in the help entry for the weave PLUS the
<mana add>. 
The mana added is oftmost mentioned in the specific weave help entries
as "add".

See also: GRASP RELEASE TIEWEAVE MAINTAIN TIE UNKNOT UNRAVEL
#0
WHERE

Usage: where <monster | player>

Tells you the location of a monster, a player or an object.

Mortals can only "where" monsters or players, and only from their own
zone.

Immortals may type 'where' without arguments to see where everybody is.

Example:

  > where
  > where torch
  > where dragon
#0
WHO

Usage: who [-n name] [-g] [-r] [-z] [-i] [-d] [-m] [-s] [-o] [-t] [-c] [-b] [-w] [-l lowlev] [-h highlev] [-a]

Lists the people currently in the game.  Some people may be invisible.
Command-line options can be used to limit the listing.  The parameters
can be specified on the command-line in any order.

Options:
	[-n name] Find a player by 'name'.
	[-g] Find a player in your guild.
	[-r] Find players in your room.
	[-z] Find players in your zone.
	[-i] Find players in-character.
	[-d] Find darkfriends.
	[-m] Find players in your club.
	[-s] Find your servants (nobility only).
	[-o] Find ogier.
	[-t] Find players in your tower (Tower guilded only).
	[-c] Find players in your aiel clan.
	[-b] Find newbies.
	[-w] Find wolfkin.
	[-l lowlev] Limit players to everyone above level 'lowlev'.
	[-h highlev] Limit players to everyone below level 'highlev'.
	[-a] Sort who list alphabetically.

Examples:

  > who -l 15 -h 25 -z
  List all levels 15 and 25 who are in your zone.
#0
WHOAMI

Usage: whoami

Displays your character's name, if you want to be sure you are who you think
you are.
#0
WIELD

Usage: wield <weapon>

When you get tired of bashing monsters with your fists, you might consider
wielding a weapon.

Example:

  > wield sword
  > wield 3.sword    (Wield the third sword in your inventory)

See also: EQUIPMENT, REMOVE, WEAR
#0
WIMPY 

Usage: wimpy <hp>

Use the WIMPY command to automatically flee once your health drops below
a certain level.

Examples:

  > wimpy 35    will make your character automatically flee a fight
                if you have less than 35 hit points.
  > wimpy 0     will turn off wimpy mode.
  > wimpy       will show you your current wimp status.

See also: FLEE, TOGGLE
