WRITE

Usage: write <object>
       write <title of board note>

In order to write a note, you need a piece of blank paper (or similar), and
a pen of some sort.  You can then type something like "write on the paper with
the pen", whereupon you'll be asked to type in your note at the keyboard.

WRITE is also used to post messages to bulletin boards.  Type HELP BOARDS
for more information.

See also: BOARDS, MAIL
#0
WT

Some people are born with the ability to talk to Wolves. These people are
(on Dragons Fang) called Wolfkin, or wolfbrothers (despite the fact that
females can have this ability as well). To communicate with other wolves, 
use the command wt. If you want to shut other wolves out of your mind, type
nowt to do so. If you want to listen to wolves again, just type nowt a second
time.

Syntax:
  wt <whatever you wish to say>

Examples:
 > wt Greetings brothers and sisters, how fare your hunt?

See also: Toggle
#0
PREFIX

Usage: prefix <prefix string>

This command will pre-pend <prefix string> to anything you subsequently type.

Your prefix string shall show up in your prompt if you're using one.

Example:
	prefix ooc
Will give you a new prompt of:
16H 12M 8V > ooc
perhaps.

Hence if you were to type "Hello!"
It would be the same as typing "ooc Hello!".
