#0
CREATION

The Creator has decided that it's time for YOU to be a
a part of the Pattern, it is time to decide your destiny
Here you can decide what class you wish to be, for details
about classes, type: HELP CLASSES.

You can also chose from what part of our realm you wish to be
and to get a list of those parts, type: HELP RACES.

To set your basic abilities, you have a number of trains
to help you out. If you think these trains are few, and that
you wont get high stats, that is correct. :) You have 200
levels to help you increase your stats. To get help about
your abilities, type HELP ABILITIES.

For help regarding the One Power and channeling, type HELP POWERS.

To see your stats, type STATS. 
When you're satisfied with your stats, type READY to start playing!
#0
CABILITIES

  To define your characters abilities, or lack of abilites
there are certain values that defines your Strength, 
Constitution, Dexterity, Intelligence, Wisdom, Charisma
Moves, Mana and Hitpoints(HP).

  Strength     - With a high strength, your character can  carry more
                 equipment, and give more damage in battle.
                      
  Constitution - With a high constitution your character   will gain
                 more Hitpoints every time you gain a level.

  Dexterity    - With a high dexterity, your character will be more
                 agile, i.e will have a higher chance to   avoid being
                 hit by an enemy.

  Intelligence - With a high intelligence, your character have a higher
                 chance to get more practice, which are used to learn skills.
                 Learning will also be easier for the intelligent character.

  Wisdom       - With a high wisdom, your character will have a higher chance
                 to gain 'trains' (See HELP POWER). 
                 
                      
  Charisma     - With high charisma, your character will gain lower prices
                 in shops, .i.e the perfect ability for the greedy. :)

  Moves        - Moves are used to move around the realm. Every move in a direcrtion\
                 will cost you moves. When your moves are 0, you'll have to rest before
                 continuing your travels.
                      
  Mana         - Mana is used for weaving the One Power. The more Mana, more powerful
                 weaves your character will be able to use.
     
  Hitpoints    - This is the amount of beating up your character will be able to take
                 before he/she dies. The more Hitpoints, the tougher, hard-hitting mobs
                 he/she will be able to fight

  To increase one of the abilities, just type the ability name, and the value you wish it
to have. I.e to get Strength 25, just type Strength 25. If you wish to lower your abilities
to gain more trains, just type (for example) Strength 5, which will give you some extra
trains.

  The cost for increasing a ability is raising with raised ability as this:


   0 - 18 -> 1 train/step
   19-25 -> 2 trains/step  
   26-39 -> 3 trains/step 

  To raise your Moves, Hitpoints or Mana, type the ability and the level you wish to have, 
for instance: Mana 110 will raise your mana from to 110.  

  You can, as with the other abilities lower your level. Mana/Moves/Hitpoints ALL costs 1 
train/10 steps, despite what your level you already have.
 
See also: POWER
#0
CPOWERS

  If you're a channeler/wisdom OR have the Spark inborn you will
have characteristics describing your strength in the Five Powers
(i.e Air, Water, Spirit, Fire and Earth). You will also be able
to spend the trains you gain as you advance in levels to increase your
strength.

  Your strength in the Five Powers will determine what
weaves your character can weave. I.e Level doesn't matter in this case.
#0
CCLASSES

With the CLASS-command you can change the class of
of your character. Just type CLASS <class-name>. The
following classes are available:

  Adventurer - An average class. Mostly a fighting-class,
               but also some knowledge about healing herbs,
               and some woodsman-skills
                  
  Soldier    - A fighting-class. Lot's of knowledge about
               different weapons, and other fighting-skills and
               not so very much more.

  Craftsman  - Knows how to work with your hands, like repearing
               stuff, and tooling it (re-stringing). Some knowledge
               about fighting, but not much.

  Thief      - Knows a lot about hiding, sneaking, stealing and to
               recognize other thieves (i.e finding their hiding-spots
               and similar). Knows some basic fighting skills too, and
               most important of all, knows how to backstab! :)

  Wisdom     - The average willage-wisdom. Lot's of knowledge about
               herbs and other healing-skills. Most often NOT a channeler
               only a person devoting his/her life as a healer, and
               as a master of herb-lore. Of course a wisdom has some knowledge\
               of fighting too.
           
  Wilder     - A person able to channel, but a person that differs from the
               channeler-class as one that has tought her/him-self to channel
               avoiding the 3/4-chance to die doing so. A wilder don't know as
               many weaves as the channeler does, although the wilders weaves
               are often more powerful that those of a channeler. Can learn about
               the same fighting-skills that an adventurer, although later in life\
               and at a higher cost.

  Channeler  - A person that have been tought have to channel, i.e  someone has
               guided the character through the critical parts of learning.
               A channeler knows more weaves than the wilder, although often
               not as powerful ones. Like the wilder, the channeler can learn
               most of the fighting-skills that an adventurer can, but later in
               life, and at a higher cost.
#0
CRACES

  Persons from different parts of the realm, has different
characteristics. As an example, a person from Shienar
might be (in average) stronger than a person from Illian.
But the Illianer might be smarter than the Shienaran.


  In Dragons Fang we've made those differences as modificatuions,
i.e. with a +3 modifier for strength, you start out with 
strength 14 instead of strength 11. So, you'll save a few
points trying to increase your strength to max. (Max will always
be 30, despite your bonuses. Another thing with races is, with the
HOME-command, yoy'll be transfered to your hometown, i.e a Shienaran
will be tranfered to Fal Dara, and a Andorian will be sent to Caemlyn.

Below are a list of 'races' and their bonuses:


