#0
primary_talent

A Primary Inborn Talent is a special ability that has been approved 
for your RP by the Storymaster. Usually, gaining such a Talent is 
as simple as sending him or her a tell, and explaining what Talent 
you want. If there's a reason why that Talent isn't acceptable, 
you will typically be told what it is, and offered suggestions 
on something else to try instead. Primary Inborn Talents can be either 
Channeling or Non-Channeling in nature; there are more Channeling-oriented 
Talents because there are more unusual things that can be done with the 
Power than there are things which can be done without it. You may have 
one Primary Inborn Talent at a time.

For further help, see: help talent_board, help secondary_talent, 
help talentlist, and help special_skills.
#0
secondary_talent

A Secondary Inborn Talent is a special ability that has been approved for 
your RP by the Storymaster. To be set with one, you must apply to the
Storymaster, and submit a log of RP as is detailed in HELP TALENT_BOARD. 
Upon satisfactory completion of the instructions found therein, you will be 
set with the requested Talent, or, should the Storymaster raise an objection 
relating to the balance of the MUD or some other such matter, offered the 
opportunity to choose something else and be set with that.

For further help, see: help talent_board, help primary_talent, help talentlist, 
and help special_skills.
#0
special_skills

A Special Skill is just what its name says - a special skill. More particularly, 
it is a skill which is only obtainable through RP with someone who already 
possesses the skill, and with the Storymaster's approval. Some Special Skills 
are also mirrored by code skills and weaves; these code abilities can be learned 
only if the Special Skill is set by the Storymaster - without a setting, the 
code ability will not function. The majority of cases can be settled by a simple 
tell to the Storymaster, but if there is an unusual circumstance, verification 
of the skill may be requested, in the form of a log of RP, the agreement of the 
teacher of the skill, or a request from a Guildleader. &RNOTE: If you die ICly, 
you will undergo a removal of any special skills which are not part of the 
standard curriculum in whatever guild you are guilded. For instance, if you are 
an Asha'man and were taught how to Travel, you would retain that special skill. 
If you were an Asha'man who was taught balefire, you would not.&n

For further help, see: help talent_board, help primary_talent, help 
secondary_talent, and help talentlist.
#0
Talent_board

Any channeling character may approach the Storymaster and request that a 
particular Inborn Talent from the help inborn helpfile should be set onto 
himself or herself. At the present time, only one inborn Talent may be selected 
in this manner. This single inborn Talent represents the character's outstanding 
area of expertise with the One Power, be it Healing, constructing Wardings or 
Illusions, or what have you. There is a procedure by which one may gain 
additional Talents, however, though these Talents are secondary in nature and 
will not justify roleplaying the same degree of skill. The procedure shall be as 
follows:

1. A Talent Board, composed of two guildleaders (drawn randomly from the Asha'man, 
Aes Sedai (Rebel and Tower), Darkfriend, Kin, and Seanchan guilds) and of two 
morts (also randomly selected from the same guilds, with each guild having one 
potential representative appointed by its guildleader) will be convened by the 
Storymaster on a fairly regular basis, perhaps every two months or so.

2. Those individuals seeking to gain a secondary or tertiary Talent must send the 
Storymaster at least one cleaned log of RP that they feel is representative of 
their ability to RP in the field in which they wish to gain the Talent (that is, 
don't send a swordplay spar if you want to be set up with Cloud Dancing). The 
Storymaster will remove the applicants' names from the logs, replacing them with 
an alias, and then submit the logs to the Talent Board for review. Thus, the 
procedure is double-blind - the judges don't know who they're judging, and the 
applicants don't know who is judging them.

3. The sitting Talent Board will score the applicants' logged RP on a scale of one 
to ten, in the following categories: Clarity (ease of understanding what is being 
done), Creativity (how unique and innovative it is), Bookishness (whether it could 
actually be done in the books, judging by what is known about the rules that govern 
channeling), Aesthetics (how it looks), and Judge's Discretion (how the judge 
-feels- about the RP). They will send the Storymaster their scores, and the total 
score for each applicant will be averaged.

4. Those applicants who score at least an average of 7.5 will be awarded the Talent 
they've requested. A lower score will result in the rejection of the request. Note: 
This criterion is applicable -only- to a secondary Talent grant. For a third Talent, 
the required average will jump considerably, to an average score of 8.75.

The Storymaster also retains the power to veto any and all awardings made by the 
Talent Board, if he or she feels that such an action is needful for the purposes 
of ensuring balance in the MUD's RP.

The choice of the Talent requested, however, is up to the applicant. If someone 
wishes to signify an extreme degree of specialization in a particular Talent, it is 
also permissible to choose a secondary Talent that matches the first - for example, 
someone with Affinity for Healing as a Primary Inborn Talent is free to choose 
Affinity for Healing as a secondary Talent, if he or she so desires. Possession of 
multiple Talents in the same field signifies high specialization in that area, and 
correspondingly high natural ability.

Finally, it must be stressed that this Talent Board does NOT function as a contest. 
Each applicant is judged and scored solely in respect to his or her RP ability, and 
for the sole purpose of determining if he or she can be deemed knowledgeable enough 
to roleplay an unusually powerful character. The results will be kept confidential. 
An applicant's score will be given out -only- to the applicant. Failure to gain a 
requested Talent does not disqualify an applicant from later attempts to do so. 
There is a MAXIMUM Talent Cap of three Talents. There will be no exceptions. Do not 
even ask.

For further help, see: help talentlist, help primary_talent, help secondary_talent, 
and help special_skills.
#0
questing
  In hopes of assisting smaller roleplay plots on the mud, rather than
skipping right to the major stuff then stopping after the massive event, the
following has been implemented.

1) If you wish to run an event, contact your  Guildleader or a Storyteller.
In the case of the latter, it is their job to execute events for your
enjoyment and if you suggest an event to them, they will seriously consider
the idea and run it, or explain why they wouldn't and help you come up with
a better idea or plot.

2) You must have more than three individuals involved in the event. Mail
the names along with the idea to the Storyteller you've chosen to run the
event.

3) Outline what you would like the Storyteller to do in the event.
  What role did you want the Storyteller to play?
  How much authority do you want the Storyteller to have oocly?
  Do you want the Storyteller to run the event, so that you are as surprised
as your companions at the outcome of the rp? Or would you rather have
full control of the event and put the Storyteller in a role of conflict
with your own or a subordinate position to your character for the rp.


  The Storytellers are here to assist in your roleplaying experience.
They are required to run events for your pleasure, but this does not mean
that they will not take quest requests. Please help the Storytellers, come up
with events that will make you have fun at Dragon's Fang.
#0
gossips and rumors
Syntax: gossip 

  This skill, given only to the Entertainers allows you to post up ic
rumors that others may have heard or observed. While the Entertainers are
the ones with access to the skill, everyone should be encouraged to
utilize their abilities in posting these rumors. Say for example, you want
to have something spread throughout the city. You're willing to perform a
shady job, or you're looking to hire some folks on for some project you've
thought of running. Maybe even you're looking for information as too a
death of a friend and you spread that you've got gold to spend and an
attentive ear to use if anyone has the information you are seeking.
  This system is great for rp so please, utilize your local Entertainer
and get them to spread a rumor for you. 

  One last note. If you cannot find an entertainer to give a rumor too, mail them and if they deem it appropriate, it'll get posted.

SEE ALSO: Entertainers
