BOARDS

Bulletin boards are the forum of inter-player communication on the MUD.
There are different bulletin boards for different purposes -- for example,
a standard mortal board, a board for immortals, a board for fun "social"
messages, etc.  Naturally, not all players may be allowed to read all
types of boards.

Type "LOOK BOARD" to see the messages already posted on a board.  Type
"WRITE <subject>" to post a message to a board; terminate a message with
a '@' as the first character on a line.  Type "READ <number>" to read a
post.  Type "REMOVE <number>" to remove your own messages.

Example:

  > look at board
  > write Am I using these boards correctly?
  [writes the message; terminates with a '@']
  > look at board
  > read 6
  > remove 6

See also: MAIL, READ, WRITE
#0
BOND

Usage: BOND <playername>

This command bonds a person as your Warder, Wife, or Minion, permanently.
By doing this, you get access to the bond channels, BDT, AMT, or MDT, depending
on the type of Bond, as well as the command bondsense.

Bonding is a One Power weave of the five flows, one that was invented not in
the Age of Legends as most spells were, but in the resurrection of the strength
of the White Tower. It places a link between the two minds of the bonder and
bondee, not telekinesis (talking on the channels is OOC), but in sensing
emotion and location of the other directly bonded. It is possible for th
bonder to bond more than one person, though these bonded cannot feel each
 other,
only the bonder. More recently, the Asha'man have learned a form of the long
known Bonding of the Sedai. It does not work quite the same; the Sedai bond
gives their Warders increased stamina and eyesight and decreased sense of pain.
For the wives and the Asha'man, it is a duller bond that is only sensory. The
Forsaken are also able to bond, but theirs is strictly OOC to allow them to
speak to their minions.

Losing a Bond is usually violent. A way to safely remove a bond is possible but
only by those truly knowledgeable in bonding - currently only the Aes Sedai.
A snapped Bond happens either when one of the two dies, or when the bonder is
stilled. In this case, the bondee has it harder than the bonder. The bondee
will feel the whiplash like a huge snap in his head, and if he does not die
immediately, he will fall into deep depression and, most often, grow cold and
try to kill himself one way or another. The best way to curb this is to rebond
him to try and fill the void of the old bond. Similarly, the bonder will feel
depression, just not as strong, and can almost always live with the loss.

See Also: BDT, AMT, BONDSENSE, POLICY BOND
#0
BUILDING BUILDER

Building is a simple process of using your imagination to create the cities,
wilderness, inns, and other areas that the players may explore. Although
time consuming and sometimes difficult when balancing equipment and mobs,
a Builder's job can be very rewarding when people move into it in order
to roleplay or just enjoy the things built within. Here at Dragon's Fang
a new builder is not required to already know how to build and utilize the
Online Creation, but it does help. Knowledge of the book series The Wheel
Of Time, however, is necessary.

\c09"Building sounds cool! How do I sign up?"\c00
The requirments for Builder include knowledge of the books, ability to be
online and meet deadlines, and good writing skill. If you wish to apply
for a Builder position, send a mail to the Headbuilder with the following
information:
1. Your name, age, and timezone
2. Any characters you play on Dragon's Fang
3. Amount of time you have mudded, here and elsewhere.
4. Any previous imm and builder experience.
5. Extent of book knowledge.
6. Areas you most like to build (ie: roads, wilderness, cities, oceans)
7. (\c01IMPORTANT\c00) Two WoT areas you are most interested in.
8. A sample of three room descriptions, completely your choice.

The Headbuilder is \c05Purdan\c00, and the application email is:
 fangbuilder@hotmail.com\c00

\c14NOTE:\c00 We are hiring as many temporary builders as we can, no experience
required, to help rebuild the world for the future opening of the new Dragon's
Fang. Although we cannot give real immortals to these temp builders, we greatly
appreciate their help and will give them both zone recognition and game
reimbursement for their time and effort. Zones that need builders include most
of the world, such as Emond's Field, Caemlyn and other Andoran regions, Fal
Moran, Shadar Logoth, Plain of Lances, Seafolk isles, Illian, and Braem Wood.
If you are interested, mail us!
