DFPOLICY

\c061)\c00    To join this guild you must be at least level 20.

\c062)\c00    Your Darkfriend character must have a story, background, and a
       description, in addition to some reason for joining the Dfguild.
       Basically the DF guild is a RP guild so you need to join for
       RP reasons.

\c063)\c00    To speak to other darkfriends use: dt <text>. Your message will
 be sent
       to all darkfriends who are logged onto the mud.
       NOTE: names will not be displayed with the message because
       dt is totally OOC.

\c064)\c00    If another character you know wants to become a darkfriend, and
 lets
       you know, inform the guildleader as soon
       as you can so they can be guilded.

\c065)\c00    If someone of a higher rank gives you an order, you must react to
 the
       order in a manner in keeping with your own standing with
       the Chosen, the Great Lord, the Hand of The Dark, and/or
       your relationship to the superiors of the person giving
       the orders.

\c066)\c00    If someone of a higher rank requests a report on your activities,
 you
       have the option of giving one, or not depending on the
       same circumstances listed in policy statement five.
       Likewise, you have the option in the degree of truth
       you give to your report, if you give one.

\c067)\c00    Your first responsibility and loyalty for your DF character
 shouldbe
       in keeping with the knowledge that disloyalty to the DFs
       can and usually does end with your character's death -
       but that it might not if you are shrewd enough.

\c068)\c00    Darkfriends can not automaticaly know what guild a person belongs
 to
       by their guild Equipment or other such clues, unless it is a really
       obvious affiliation such as Whitecloak battle armor, Gleeman patchwork
       cloak, and so forth. (Basically just use common sense)

\c069)\c00   You are allowed to join another guild (if you do not already
 belong
       to one) after you become a Darkfriend.

\c0610)\c00  If you are IC'ly known by a member to have betrayed the guild in
 some
       fashion, your Darkfriend character will almost certainly
       be killed in reprisal, unless someone powerful enough to
       save you comes to your aid.

\c0611)\c00  The only way to leave the guild is to be willing to ICly be a
 marked
       target for the rest of that character's IC existence.

\c0612)\c00  If you have an alt who is not in the Darkfriend guild, and use
       Darkfriend guild knowledge with that character, disciplinary action
       will be taken that is in keeping with the abuse of IC knowledge OOCly
       (for that is what you will have done).

\c0613)\c00  You will be expected to attend all Darkfriend guild meetings, and 
if
       you are unable to attend, please inform the guildleaders BEFORE the
       meeting.

\c0614)\c00  Darkfriend book characters will start with the level, rank,
 equipment,
       skills, weaves, money, and so forth that will be deemed appropriate
       by Shai'tan and Shaidar.

\c0616)\c00  Darkfriend book characters who are also a member of another guild 
can
       only be assigned by Shai'tan and Shaidar in conjunction with the
       other GL(s).

\c0617)\c00 If another character has proof that your character is a member of
       the Darkfriend guild, it will be an IC reason(in most cases) for them
       to try and kill your character, and it will also be a reason for
       other Dfs to kill you (again assuming that they gain IC knowledge
       that your character has been unmasked).

\c0618)\c00  Darkfriend guild members have the option of choosing Darkfriend
 guildeq
       or the guildeq of their regular guild (but only in such cases
       when the guildleader of their regular guild -also- allows this
       option). Guild skills will be restricted and given out on the
       basis of RP to the appriopriate ranks and -type- of ranks.

\c0619)\c00 Dreadlords may at no time teach skills to anyone other than
       Dreadlords. The only exception to this, is a Chosen may direct a
       Dreadlord to teach something to a Darkfriend. However, any such
       instant must be reported to a DF Guildleader and the logs of the
       roleplay(both the order and the lesson) emailed in(Note: emailed,
       mudmail is unacceptable), without exception. (The Chosen will
       also consult with the Master Dreadlord to determine whether the
       skill is permissable to allow a darkfriend/non DL to acquire).

\c01See also: \c07DARKFRIEND GUILDS\c00
