See also: UNDARK
#200
UPTIME

Usage: uptime

Displays when the game was booted and calculates how long ago that was.
#200
USERS

Usage: users [switches]

USERS gives a list of all sockets (i.e., connections) currently active on the
MUD.  The multi-column display shows the socket number (used by DC), class,
level, and name of the player connected, connection state, idle time, and
hostname.

The following switches are available:

-k or -o   Show only outlaws (killers and thieves).
-p         Show only sockets in the playing sockets.
-d         Show only non-playing (deadweight) sockets.
-l min-max Show only sockets whose characters are from level min to max.
-n <name>  Show the socket with <name> associated with it.
-h <host>  Show all sockets from <host>.
-c list    Show only sockets whose characters' classes are in list.

See also: DC, SLOWNS
#200
VNUM

Usage: vnum <mob | obj> <name>

Gives a list of the virtual numbers of objects or mobiles which have the
specified name.

Examples:

  > vnum obj ring
  1. [  904] a platinum ring
  2. [ 2543] a seashell ring
  3. [ 2588] a small emerald ring

  > vnum mob dragon
  1. [    1] Puff
  2. [  908] the dragon turtle
  3. [ 2548] the Master of Illusions
#200
VSTAT

Usage: vstat < mob | obj > <virtual number>

Used to stat a prototypical mobile or object by virtual number.

Examples:

  > vstat obj 3000
  > vstat mob 3001

See also: LOAD, STAT, VNUM
#200
WIZHELP

Usage: wizhelp

Gives a list of the special commands available at your level.
#200
WIZLOCK

Usage: wizlock [value]

WIZLOCK allows you to restrict the game.  WIZLOCK 1 prevents new characters
from being created.  WIZLOCK n, 2 <= n <= 34, prevents new characters and
allows only characters level n and above to log on.  WIZLOCK with no argument
displays the current WIZLOCK level.

See also: BAN
#200
WIZNET ;

The immortal communication channel.

Usage: wiznet [ '@' | '+' | '-' | '#' ] [<text>]

Examples:

  >; <text>    - just sends text
  >; @         - shows all gods that are on and visible to you
               - also shows if the gods who are visible to you are writing

This code was provided by Gnort.

See also: NOWIZ
#200
WSET

Usage: wset <player> <rank>

This command sets the wolfrank within the Wolfkin subguild for a player.
Can only be used on guilded players. To get a list of wolfkin ranks 
type "wolfranks"
#200
ZEDIT

Usage: zedit <room vnum>
       zedit [save | new] <zone>

Edits existing or adds new zone commands to the database.
To make mobs load, doors close or objs appear when there is a zone reset,
this is the command to use.
This command makes you enter a menu driven OLC system.

The second alternative makes you save your changes onto disk or create a new zone.

See ZEDIT2 for a description of menu options.

See also: OEDIT, REDIT, SEDIT, MEDIT
#200
ZEDIT2

When you type zedit, the following screen is displayed.

-=-=-=-=-=-=--=-=-=-=-=-=--=-=-=-=-=-=--=-=-=-=-=-=-
Room number: &c10100&n             Room zone: &c100&n
&gZ&n) Zone name   : &yCaemlyn&n
&gL&n) Lifespan    : &y4 minutes&n
&gT&n) Top of zone : &y10500&n
&gR&n) Reset Mode  : &yNormal reset.&n
[Command list]
0 - <END OF LIST>
&gN&n) New command.
&gE&n) Edit a command.
&gD&n) Delete a command.
&gQ&n) Quit
Enter your choice : 
-=-=-=-=-=-=--=-=-=-=-=-=--=-=-=-=-=-=--=-=-=-=-=-=-

The various entries are explained below.

Z. &yZone name&n: This is the name of the zone, which is arbitrary, but
              should be accurate.
L. &yLifespan&n: This determines the time interval between which the zedit
             command list is executed again.  Set it to a low value if you 
             want the zone to reset often.  Generally, 30 minutes is a
             reasonable value.
T. &yTop of zone&n: This entry sets the highest room vnum in the present 
                zone.  This should only be set by the Head Builder.
N. &yNew Command&n: This option inserts a command into the command list.  The
                selection places you in a new menu that looks like this:
         -=-=-=-=-=-=--=-=-=-=-=-=--=-=-=-=-=-=--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
         &gM&n) Load Mobile to room             &gO&n) Load Object to room
         &gE&n) Equip mobile with object        &gG&n) Give an object to a mobile
         &gP&n) Put object in another object    &gD&n) Open/Close/Lock a Door
         &gR&n) Remove an object from the room  &gL&n) Load mob on obj (sleeping)
         &gT&n) Load mob on obj (sitting)       &gU&n) Load obj ON obj
         What sort of command will this be? : 
         -=-=-=-=-=-=--=-=-=-=-=-=--=-=-=-=-=-=--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
The entries are self-explanatory.  If this is not the first command on this
list, you will be asked if it is dependent on the success of the previous
one.  If the command is an Equip, Put, or Give command, you should answer
yes.  You will then be asked a few questions depending on what options you
selected, such as the vnums of the mobiles or objects you wish to load.
Note also that the last three options are only used with furniture items.
E. &yEdit a command&n: Changes an existing command in the list.
D. &yDelete a command&n: Removes an existing command from the list.

NOTE: If you use zedit to open/close/lock a door, please remember to do
the same on both sides of the door.  If you delete a command, delete all
those that depend on it, if any, or replace it as appropriate.  

Q. &yQuit&n: This exits the zone editor.  Once again, you must use the 
command 'zedit save <zone num>' to permanently save your changes.
#200
ZRESET

Usage: zreset < zone | '*' | '.' >

Used to force a zone to reset.  '*' forces all zones to reset.  '.' forces
the zone you are in to reset.

See also: SHOW -> ZONES
#200
WAGON

A wagon is both a room and an object, and consequently must be created using
both the oedit and redit editors.  It is a room that can be entered using 
the 'enter' command as opposed to going through an exit, and generally
requires using the 'leave' command for egress.  As the name implies, a common
usage is to create wagon objects that can be pulled from room to room and
entered at will, but they do not have to be utilized for vehicular purposes.
Wagon objects can be used as entrances to other rooms, or even to other zones,
and they are often stationary, such as cave entrances.  In such a case, 
be sure to flag them as !PULL, otherwise, anyone can drag them around.

To create a wagon, you must create an object and a room that both have the
same vnum, and both must be flagged as wagon.  The object must not be
able to be picked up.  
